## Rules

### BACK-001: Async Patterns
severity: ERROR
scope: all Node.js/TypeScript service functions
rule: All asynchronous operations MUST use async/await. Callback-based patterns are prohibited in new code. Promise chains (.then/.catch) MUST be replaced with async/await.
threshold: max_function_lines=30, max_complexity=10
example_correct: |
  async function getUser(id: string): Promise<User> {
    return await userRepository.findById(id);
  }
example_incorrect: |
  function getUser(id, callback) {
    userRepository.findById(id, (err, user) => callback(err, user));
  }

### BACK-002: TypeScript Strict Mode
severity: ERROR
scope: all TypeScript files
rule: All TypeScript files MUST compile with strict mode enabled. The use of `any` type is prohibited without an explicit ESLint disable comment explaining the reason. All function parameters and return values MUST be explicitly typed.
threshold: max_function_lines=30
example_correct: |
  function processOrder(order: Order): Promise<Result<void, string>> { ... }
example_incorrect: |
  function processOrder(order: any): any { ... }  // any — prohibited
